HIV/AIDS: Sin ta ba da rahoton karuwar kashi 14 cikin 100 na sababbin cututtuka
Kasar Sin ta ba da rahoton cewa yawan mutanen da ke dauke da cutar HIV da AIDS ya karu da kashi 14 cikin 100.
Mutane fiye da 820,000 ne suka kamu da cutar a kasar, kamar yadda hukumomin kiwon lafiya suka ce.
An samu karin sabbin shari'o'i 40,000 a cikin kashi na biyu na shekarar 2018 kadai.
Yawancin sababbin cututtuka na jima'i ne, kuma wannan canji ne ga abin da ya faru a baya.
A al'adance, cutar HIV tana yaduwa cikin sauri saboda karuwar jini a wasu yankunan kasar Sin.
Amma a wannan hanyar, adadin mutanen da ke kamuwa da cutar ta HIV ya ragu zuwa kusan sifili, kamar yadda hukumomin kiwon lafiya na kasar Sin suka ce a wani taro a lardin Yunnan.
Duk da haka, a kowace shekara, adadin mutanen da ke dauke da cutar HIV da AIDS a kasar Sin ya karu da mutane 100,000.
Yada HIV ta hanyar jima'i babbar matsala ce ga al'ummar LGBT a kasar Sin.
An haramta jima'i a kasar Sin a shekara ta 1997, amma nuna bambanci ga LGBTs ya zama ruwan dare.
Bisa ga dabi'un da kasar ta nuna, bincike ya nuna cewa kashi 70 zuwa 90 cikin 100 na maza da suka yi jima'i da maza sun auri mace.
Yawancin cututtuka da ake watsawa a cikin dangantaka suna faruwa ne ta hanyar amfani da kariya ta jima'i.
Tun daga 2003, gwamnatin kasar Sin ta ba da umarnin samun damar yin amfani da maganin cutar AIDS a duniya a matsayin wani ɓangare na ƙoƙarin magance matsalar.
