Yayin da manyan 'yan Republican ke jiran su kuma suna kare dan takararsu na Brett Kavanaugh zuwa Kotun Koli a gaban zargin da ake yi da cin zarafin jima'i, masu bincike sun yi gargadin cewa za a samu raguwa, musamman tsakanin mata, a zaben tsakiyar majalisa na gaba.
A halin yanzu, akwai motsin rai mai yawa game da wannan batun, kuma yawancin 'yan Republican sun yi rajista suna nuna cewa suna son ci gaba da jefa kuri'a.
Ba za a iya komawa baya a kan waɗannan batutuwa ba, "in ji Grant Reeher, wani farfesa a Makarantar Maxwell na Jami'ar Syracyse, game da wani labarin da aka buga a ranar Asabar ga The Hill.
Reeher ya ce yana shakkar cewa Sanata Jeff Flake na Arizona zai iya matsa lamba don gudanar da bincike na FBI don ya kwantar da hankalin masu jefa kuri'a masu fushi.
"Mata ba za su manta da abin da ya faru a jiya ba - ba za su manta da gobe ba, kuma ba ma a watan Nuwamba ba", in ji Karine Jean-Pierre, babban mai ba da shawara da kuma kakakin kungiyar ta MoveOn, a cewar jaridar Washington, D.C.
A safiyar Juma'a, masu zanga-zangar da ke ihu "Watan Nuwamba na zuwa!" suna zanga-zangar a gaban Majalisar Dattawa cewa 'yan Republican da ke kula da Kwamitin Shari'a sun yanke shawarar ci gaba da zaben Kavanaugh duk da shaidar Dr. Christine Blasey Ford, ya bayyana a Mic.
"Hakika, ƙarfin hali da kuma motsawar 'yan Democrat ba za su kasance ba", in ji mai bincike na siyasa mai zaman kansa Stu Rothenberg ga shafin yanar gizon labarai.
